This paper deals with a multi-robot payload transport system, which involves designing a system of robots that work together to transport a payload. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the optimization of the system, which involves decision-making and scheduling, which could fall under machine learning (cs.MA), control systems (cs.SY), or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents simulations and experiments with real robots, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or robotics (cs.RO).
